class Session: 
61class Session:
62    def __init__(
63        self,
64        client: Client,
65        host: str = "localhost",
66        port: int = 1545,
67        debug: bool = False,
68    ):
69        self.client = client
70        self.host = host
71        self.port = port
72        self._debug = debug
73
74    def exec(self, command: Command) -> RawOutput:
75        args: list[str] = [
76            str(self.client.rac_path),
77            f"{self.host}:{self.port}",
78        ] + command.args
79        if self._debug:
80            print("[DEBUG]", args)
81        try:
82            process = run(
83                args,
84                capture_output=True,
85                text=True,
86                encoding="cp866",
87            )
88            if process.returncode != 0:
89                raise errors.handler(process.stderr)
90            else:
91                if self._debug:
92                    print(process.stdout)
93                return RawOutput(process.stdout)
94        except FileNotFoundError:
95            raise errors.RACNotFoundError
96
97    def call(self, command: Command) -> None:
98        self.exec(command)

class AsyncSession: 
10class AsyncSession:
11    def __init__(
12        self,
13        async_client: AsyncClient,
14        host: str = "localhost",
15        port: int = 1545,
16        debug: bool = False,
17    ) -> None:
18        self.client = async_client
19        self.host = host
20        self.port = port
21        self._debug = debug
22
23    async def async_exec(self, command: Command):
24        args: list[str] = [
25            f"{self.host}:{self.port}",
26        ] + command.args
27        if self._debug:
28            print("[DEBUG]", args)
29        try:
30            process = await asyncio.create_subprocess_exec(
31                self.client.rac_path,
32                *args,
33                stdout=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE,
34                stderr=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE,
35            )
36            stdout, stderr = await process.communicate()
37            if process.returncode != 0:
38                stderr = stderr.decode(encoding="cp866")
39                raise errors.handler(stderr)
40            else:
41                stdout = stdout.decode(encoding="cp866")
42                if self._debug:
43                    print(stdout)
44                return RawOutput(stdout)
45        except FileNotFoundError:
46            raise errors.RACNotFoundError
47
48    async def async_call(self, command: Command):
49        await self.async_exec(command)

31                self.client.rac_path,
32                *args,
33                stdout=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE,
34                stderr=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE,
35            )
36            stdout, stderr = await process.communicate()
37            if process.returncode != 0:
38                stderr = stderr.decode(encoding="cp866")
39                raise errors.handler(stderr)

 6class Agent:
 7    class Admin:
 8        @staticmethod
 9        def list(
10            session: Session,
11            agent_user: str | None = None,
12            agent_pwd: str | None = None,
13        ):
14            return session.exec(
15                Command(
16                    Arg("agent"),
17                    Arg(agent_user, "--agent-user={}"),
18                    Arg(agent_pwd, "--agent-pwd={}"),
19                    Arg("admin"),
20                    Arg("list"),
21                )
22            ).to_list()
23
24        @staticmethod
25        def register(
26            session: Session,
27            name: str,
28            pwd: str | None = None,
29            auth: str = "pwd",
30            descr: str | None = None,
31            os_user: str | None = None,
32            agent_user: str | None = None,
33            agent_pwd: str | None = None,
34        ):
35            return session.call(
36                Command(
37                    Arg("agent"),
38                    Arg(agent_user, "--agent-user={}"),
39                    Arg(agent_pwd, "--agent-pwd={}"),
40                    Arg("admin"),
41                    Arg("register"),
42                    Arg(name, "--name={}"),
43                    Arg(pwd, "--pwd={}"),
44                    Arg(descr, "--descr={}"),
45                    Arg(auth, "--auth={}"),
46                    Arg(os_user, "--os-user={}"),
47                )
48            )
49
50        @staticmethod
51        def remove(
52            session: Session,
53            name: str,
54            agent_user: str | None = None,
55            agent_pwd: str | None = None,
56        ):
57            return session.call(
58                Command(
59                    Arg("agent"),
60                    Arg(agent_user, "--agent-user={}"),
61                    Arg(agent_pwd, "--agent-pwd={}"),
62                    Arg("admin"),
63                    Arg("remove"),
64                    Arg(name, "--name={}"),
65                ),
66            )

69    def version(session: Session):
70        return session.exec(Command(Arg("agent"), Arg("version"))).to_str()

class AsyncInfobase: 
  7class AsyncInfobase:
  8    @staticmethod
  9    async def info(
 10        session: AsyncSession,
 11        cluster: str,
 12        infobase: str | None = None,
 13        name: str | None = None,
 14        infobase_user: str | None = None,
 15        infobase_pwd: str | None = None,
 16        cluster_user: str | None = None,
 17        cluster_pwd: str | None = None,
 18    ):
 19        output = await session.async_exec(
 20            Command(
 21                Arg("infobase"),
 22                Arg(cluster, "--cluster={}"),
 23                Arg(cluster_user, "--cluster-user={}"),
 24                Arg(cluster_pwd, "--cluster-pwd={}"),
 25                Arg("info"),
 26                Arg(infobase, "--infobase={}"),
 27                Arg(name, "--name={}"),
 28                Arg(infobase_user, "--infobase-user={}"),
 29                Arg(infobase_pwd, "--infobase-pwd={}"),
 30            )
 31        )
 32        return output.to_dict()

 34    class Summary:

class Rule: 
  6class Rule:
  7    @staticmethod
  8    def apply(
  9        session: Session,
 10        cluster: str,
 11        partial: bool = False,
 12        cluster_user: str | None = None,
 13        cluster_pwd: str | None = None,
 14    ):
 15        return session.call(
 16            Command(
 17                Arg("rule"),
 18                Arg(cluster, "--cluster={}"),
 19                Arg(cluster_user, "--cluster-user={}"),
 20                Arg(cluster_pwd, "--cluster-pwd={}"),
 21                Arg("apply"),
 22                Flag(partial, "--partial"),
 23            )
 24        )
 25
 26    @staticmethod
 27    def info(
 28        session: Session,
 29        cluster: str,
 30        server: str,
 31        rule: str,
 32        cluster_user: str | None = None,
 33        cluster_pwd: str | None = None,
 34    ):

class AsyncProfile:

  9    async def list(
 10        session: AsyncSession,
 11        cluster: str,
 12        cluster_user: str | None = None,
 13        cluster_pwd: str | None = None,
 14    ):
 15        output = await session.async_exec(
 16            Command(
 17                Arg("profile"),
 18                Arg(cluster, "--cluster={}"),
 19                Arg(cluster_user, "--cluster-user={}"),
 20                Arg(cluster_pwd, "--cluster-pwd={}"),
 21                Arg("list"),
 22            )
 23        )
 24        return output.to_list()

 43        cluster_pwd: str | None = None,
 44    ):
 45        return await session.async_call(
 46            Command(
 47                Arg("profile"),
 48                Arg(cluster, "--cluster={}"),
 49                Arg(cluster_user, "--cluster-user={}"),
 50                Arg(cluster_pwd, "--cluster-pwd={}"),
